'''Capital punishment in [[Tajikistan]]''' is allowed by Article 18 of the 1999 [[Constitution of Tajikistan]], which provides: {{quote|"Every person has the right to life. No person may be deprived of life except by the verdict of a court for a very serious crime."<ref>[http://unpan1.un.org/intradoc/groups/public/documents/untc/unpan003670.htm The 1994 Constitution of the Republic of Tajikistan], English translation (raw draft)</ref>}}
The last known execution took place in 2004.{{cn|date=January 2017}} That same year, a moratorium was issued on capital punishment by president [[Emomali Rahmon]].

Tajikistan is not signatory to the [[Second Optional Protocol to the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights]], which aims to abolish the [[death penalty]].<ref>[https://www.amnesty.org/en/death-penalty/ratification-of-international-treaties Ratification of Second Optional Protocol on abolition of death penalty]</ref>

