{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox organization | image = | formation = | type = [[Professional association]] | headquarters = [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = Stefan De Hert | budget = | name = European Society of Anaesthesiology | location = Europe }}
The '''European Society of Anaesthesiology''' ('''ESA'''), established in its current form in 2005,<ref name="ESAnews13">{{cite web | url = http://newsletter.esahq.org/wp-content/uploads/ESA_NEWSLETTER_AUTUMN_2013.pdf | title = The European Society of Anaesthesiology 8 years on, have our hopes and intentions been realised? | publisher = European Society of Anaesthesiology | accessdate = 1 September 2018 | author = Sir Peter Simpson | work = ESA News | date = Autumn 2013 }}</ref> is the largest association of physicians specialising in [[anaesthesiology]] in Europe.
Its stated mission is "to aim for the highest standards of practice and safety in [[anaesthesia]], [[perioperative medicine]], [[intensive care medicine|intensive care]], [[critical emergency medicine]] and [[pain medicine|pain treatment]] through education, research and professional development throughout Europe."<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.esahq.org/about-us/the-esa/about-the-esa | title = About the ESA | accessdate = 1 September 2018 }}</ref> The Society also administers an [[academic journal]], the ''[[European Journal of Anaesthesiology]]'' (EJA).<ref name="EJA">{{cite web | url = https://journals.lww.com/ejanaesthesiology/Pages/AbouttheJournal.aspx | title = About the Journal | website = European Journal of Anaesthesiology | accessdate = 1 September 2018 }}</ref> It was formed in 2005 to unify the roles of three previous organisations: the European Academy of Anaesthesiology (EAA) dating from 1978, the former European Society of Anaesthesiologists (ESA) established in 1992, and the Confederation of European National Societies of Anaesthesiology (CENSA).<ref name="ESAnews13" /><ref name="Eger Saidman Westhorpe 2013 p. 510">{{cite book | last = Eger | first = E.I. | last2 = Saidman | first2 = L.J. | last3 = Westhorpe | first3 = R.N. | title = The Wondrous Story of Anesthesia | publisher = Springer New York | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-1-4614-8441-7 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=H--3BAAAQBAJ&pg=PA510 | access-date = 1 October 2018 | page = 510 }}</ref><ref name="Yentis Hirsch Ip 2018 p. 218">{{cite book | last = Yentis | first = S.M. | last2 = Hirsch | first2 = N.P. | last3 = Ip | first3 = J. | title = Anaesthesia and Intensive Care A-Z E-Book: An Encyclopaedia of Principles and Practice | publisher = Elsevier Health Sciences | series = FRCA Study Guides | year = 2018 | isbn = 978-0-7020-7187-4 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=LqJTDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA218 | access-date = 1 October 2018 | page = 218 }}</ref>
