{{refimprove|date=February 2010}} The '''Gold Humanism Honor Society''' ('''GHHS''') is a national [[honor society]] that honors senior medical students, residents, role-model physician teachers and other exemplars recognized for demonstrated excellence in clinical care, leadership, compassion and dedication to service. It was created by the [[Arnold P. Gold Foundation]] for Humanism in Medicine.
==Purpose== The purpose of GHHS is to recognize the importance of humanistic care and to honor physicians who achieve this excellence.
