{|{{Infobox ship begin |infobox caption=}} <!-- commercial vessels --><!-- caption: yes, nodab, or <caption text> --> {{Infobox ship image |Ship image=[[File:Vpered.jpg|Vpered|300px]] |Ship caption=''Vpered'' during her service as a [[hospital ship]] in [[World War I]]. }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship flag=[[File:Naval Ensign of Russia.svg|40px|Russian Naval Ensign]] [[Imperial Russia]] |Ship name=*''SS Vpered'' (1898-1914) *([[Image: Red_Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]) ''HS Vpered'' (1914-1916) |Ship namesake= |Ship owner=Azov Black Sea Steamship Co. |Ship operator= |Ship registry=[[File:Naval Ensign of Russia.svg|40px|Russian Naval Ensign]] [[Imperial Russia]], [[Rostov]] |Ship route= |Ship ordered=1898 |Ship builder=Stabilimento Tecnico |Ship original cost= |Ship yard number= |Ship way number= |Ship laid down=1898 |Ship launched=1898 |Ship completed=1898 |Ship christened= |Ship acquired= |Ship maiden voyage=1898 |Ship in service=1898 |Ship out of service= |Ship identification= |Ship fate=Torpedoed and sunk 8 July 1916 |Ship status= |Ship notes= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship class= |Ship type=[[Passenger ship]]/[[Hospital ship]] |Ship tonnage={{GRT|859}} |Ship length= |Ship beam= |Ship height= |Ship draught= |Ship draft= |Ship depth= |Ship Armament= |Ship decks= |Ship deck clearance= |Ship ramps= |Ship ice class= |Ship sail plan= |Ship power= |Ship propulsion= |Ship speed= |Ship capacity= |Ship crew= |Ship notes= }} |}
'''HS ''Vpered''''' ({{lang-ru|госпитальное судно "Вперёд"}}) was a [[Russia]]n [[hospital ship]] that was torpedoed by the [[Imperial German Navy]] [[submarine]] [[SM U-38|SM ''U-38'']] on 8 July 1916.<ref name=NHE/>
== Construction == '''SS ''Vpered''''' was built at the Stabilimento Tecnico shipyard in [[Trieste]], [[Italy]], in 1898 for Azov Black Sea Steamship Company. She was [[Ship naming and launching|launched]] and completed in the same year. The ship was assessed at {{GRT|859}}.<ref name=NHE>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?170579 |title=SS Vperiod (Вперед) (+1916) |publisher=wrecksite.eu |date=3 October 2010 |accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>
== World War I and sinking == ''Vpered'' was converted into a [[hospital ship]] when [[World War I]] broke out and operated in the [[Black Sea]] to evacuate wounded Russian soldiers from the [[Eastern Front (World War I)|Eastern Front]].<ref name=NHE/>
On 8 July 1916, ''Vpered'' was [[torpedo]]ed by the [[Imperial German Navy]] [[submarine]] [[SM U-38|SM ''U-38'']] in the Black Sea between Rizeh and [[Batum]]. She sank shortly after. She was not carrying any wounded soldiers at the time, but seven people died in her sinking. Her survivors were saved a short time later.<ref>П.Г.Усенко (P.G.Usenko), [http://www.history.org.ua/JournALL/journal/2005/6/5.pdfЗ IСТОРIЇ ВЕЛИКОЇ ВIЙНИ 1914–1917 рр. НА ЧОРНОМУ МОРI]{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} (From the history of the Great War of the 1914-1917 on the Black Sea). Page 80. {{ua icon}}</ref>
The [[Russian Empire]] claimed that [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] forces sank ''Vperiod'' rather than the Germans.<ref name="NYT.1916">{{cite web |date= December 31, 1916|url = https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1916/12/31/100233755.pdf|title = Peace Movement Diverts Attention at Year's End from Battlefields to Chancelleries of Belligerents and Principal Neutral Capitals.|format = PDF|publisher = [[The New York Times]]| accessdate = August 24, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref> The [[Ottoman Empire]] replied that both ships were sunk by [[Naval mine|mines]].
