'''''Vismia baccifera''''' is a tropical plant used by indigenous peoples in South America, in Colombian Amazon as well as Brazil, infused as traditional medicine.  It has been demonstrated to have great antitumor capability in kidney<ref>[https://medicalxpress.com/news/2018-09-antitumour-mechanism-amazonian-human-cancer.html The antitumour mechanism of an Amazonian plant in human cancer cells is deciphered ]</ref> and liver<ref>[https://www.drugtargetreview.com/news/35851/amazonian-plant-antitumour-mechanisms/ Amazonian plant provides antitumour activity]</ref> by inducing massive oxidative stress in cancer cells, but not healthy cells, leading to rapid death of cancer cells.

